value.name: CoaXPress - Wikipedia
value.snippet: CoaXPress (CXP) is a digital interface standard developed for high speed image data transmission in machine vision applications. The name is a portmanteau of 'express' (as in express train ) and ' coaxial ' to emphasize CoaXPress is faster than other standards (e.g. Camera Link , or GigE Vision ) and uses 75 ohm coaxial cables as the physical transmission medium.
